WEBVTT

00:33.698 --> 00:36.141
Welcome back to our study of the book of Proverbs.

00:36.501 --> 00:37.662
We are in chapter 7.

00:39.184 --> 00:41.887
And I'm going to start reading in verse 10, okay?

00:42.388 --> 00:46.232
So open up your Bibles, Proverbs, chapter 7, and verse 10.

00:48.695 --> 00:53.360
And behold, a woman comes to meet him, dressed as a harlot and cunning of heart.

00:53.940 --> 00:55.602
She is boisterous and rebellious.

00:56.523 --> 00:58.025
Her feet do not remain at home.

00:58.425 --> 01:02.610
She is now in the streets, now in the squares, and lurks by every corner.

01:03.650 --> 01:10.919
So she seizes him and kisses him, and with a brazen face she says to him, I was due to offer peace offerings.

01:11.320 --> 01:12.922
Today I have paid my vows.

01:13.783 --> 01:17.728
Therefore I have come out to meet you, to seek your presence earnestly.

01:18.329 --> 01:19.290
And I have found you.

01:20.011 --> 01:24.097
I have spread my couch with coverings, with colored linens from Egypt.

01:24.818 --> 01:28.242
I have sprinkled my bed with mirth, aloes and cinnamon.

01:29.154 --> 01:31.618
Come let us drink our fill of love until morning.

01:31.658 --> 01:33.722
Let us delight ourselves with caresses.

01:34.543 --> 01:39.191
For my husband is not at home and he has gone on a long journey.

01:39.271 --> 01:41.435
He has taken a bag of money with him.

01:42.477 --> 01:46.824
At the full moon, he will come home with her many persuasions.

01:47.044 --> 01:50.230
She entices him with her flattering lips.

01:51.051 --> 01:52.494
She seduces him.

01:53.515 --> 01:55.058
Okay, let's go to the Lord in prayer.

01:57.794 --> 02:00.639
Father, we come before you in the name of your son.

02:00.699 --> 02:12.497
And Lord, this is a difficult text, an ugly text, but a necessary one to warn us of the dangers of sin.

02:14.300 --> 02:25.618
Please, Father, I pray that you would work in the heart of the children and the youth who are studying proverbs with me, that they would see and they would understand

02:27.298 --> 02:35.526
that we live behind enemy lines and that in many ways this world is a spiritually dangerous place.

02:36.987 --> 02:56.626
Lord, I pray that you would increase the fear of the Lord and all of the ones who will hear this series, that they would walk in holiness, that they would separate themselves, not just from the world, but that they would separate themselves unto your son, Jesus Christ.

02:57.570 --> 02:59.814
Lord, help us now as we teach through this.

03:00.515 --> 03:02.318
In Jesus' name, amen.

03:03.580 --> 03:05.923
Well, let me do something of a review, okay?

03:05.963 --> 03:21.969
First of all, this text is referring to a woman who is unfaithful to her husband and her family, and she's also more than willing to do damage to others for the sake of her own delight, her own enjoyment, her own pleasure.

03:22.750 --> 03:25.394
But the way we're going to look at this, because

03:25.538 --> 03:31.827
All of her characteristics are also the very characteristics we find in the world.

03:32.247 --> 03:52.375
When I refer to the world, I'm not talking about the globe, I'm talking about that order, that system of thought, ideology, attitudes, actions, deeds that are contrary to the nature and will of God.

03:53.056 --> 03:54.578
We live in a fallen world.

03:55.778 --> 04:00.905
and trying to live as Christians in the midst of that fallen world can be extremely difficult.

04:00.985 --> 04:01.326
Why?

04:02.087 --> 04:08.495
Because just like this woman who's trying to tempt a young man to do something very, very wrong.

04:09.336 --> 04:20.371
So the world tries to draw us away from Christ and to do those things which are contrary to his holy nature and his holy will.

04:21.233 --> 04:23.736
So as we go on, we're going to look at this.

04:23.836 --> 04:25.298
Now we've studied a big

04:25.378 --> 04:26.239
portion of this.

04:26.279 --> 04:28.723
So I want to review what we've seen thus far.

04:29.444 --> 04:39.881
First of all, remember this woman, she is symbolizing for us the world and it's attempt to attract us away from Christ.

04:40.662 --> 04:46.351
So first of all, in verse 10, the world's outward appearance hides its inner reality.

04:46.391 --> 04:47.232
Look in verse 10.

04:49.335 --> 04:51.719
Let me get back over there.

04:51.739 --> 04:53.682
And behold, the woman comes to meet him

04:53.954 --> 04:56.157
dressed as a harlot and cunning of heart.

04:56.738 --> 04:58.841
The world, let me put it this way.

04:58.921 --> 05:07.653
It dresses itself up in a way that seeks to draw us, to attract us, and to tempt us.

05:08.034 --> 05:12.841
So outside though, it may be quite beautiful, but inside.

05:13.642 --> 05:16.306
Well, Jesus described it as dead men's bones.

05:16.806 --> 05:20.391
So the world's outward appearance hides its inner reality.

05:21.012 --> 05:22.194
Also in verse 10,

05:22.306 --> 05:26.751
It says that this woman is cunning, the world is cunning.

05:27.352 --> 05:32.839
And literally, in the Hebrew, it's kept secret of heart.

05:33.900 --> 05:38.025
What does it mean that she's not showing her true intentions?

05:39.127 --> 05:41.710
The world doesn't show its true intentions.

05:42.291 --> 05:49.519
The world will sometimes come alongside of us like it's our friend, like it wants to help us, even that it wants to protect us from God.

05:51.001 --> 05:51.602
But the

05:51.810 --> 05:57.177
the inward intention that sometimes we can't see is evil and harmful.

05:57.457 --> 06:07.289
And if we listen to the world, if we just look at the propaganda, we will find ourselves in a very, very dark place from which we may not be able to return.

06:07.950 --> 06:09.452
So the world is also cunning.

06:09.492 --> 06:12.616
And then in verse 11, look at this woman.

06:12.976 --> 06:14.138
She is boisterous.

06:14.398 --> 06:16.240
The world is boisterous.

06:16.521 --> 06:20.946
The idea here is that all around this woman,

06:21.154 --> 06:22.416
There is turmoil.

06:23.257 --> 06:24.638
There is chaos.

06:25.159 --> 06:26.140
There is loudness.

06:26.240 --> 06:27.582
There's, there's not peace.

06:28.703 --> 06:32.007
And what you'll find is that the world makes a lot of noise.

06:32.948 --> 06:37.754
But when all the noise dies down, it just has misery and no peace.

06:38.615 --> 06:48.147
What we're looking for in life is not a lot of clamoring or chaos, but order and peace.

06:48.667 --> 06:50.770
And only the Lord can give that to us.

06:51.618 --> 06:52.359
not the world.

06:53.240 --> 06:55.702
Also in verse 11, she is rebellious.

06:56.042 --> 06:58.585
The world is rebellious.

06:59.105 --> 07:03.730
It's rebellious against all that is right, all that is good.

07:04.090 --> 07:10.276
It is rebellious against the character of God and the will of God as it is revealed in Scripture.

07:10.756 --> 07:15.541
Sinclair Ferguson said this, men hate God's will because it's not theirs.

07:15.981 --> 07:17.343
You see, God is good.

07:18.544 --> 07:19.325
He's holy.

07:19.865 --> 07:20.786
He's righteous.

07:20.898 --> 07:23.982
He's loving and His will conforms to that.

07:24.923 --> 07:29.949
So everything He tells us to do is loving and kind and good.

07:30.670 --> 07:32.692
But you see, fallen man is not that way.

07:32.772 --> 07:41.823
The Bible says clearly that we were born with a corrupt moral nature and we long for evil and we long to do evil deeds.

07:41.843 --> 07:50.834
And it is only in Christ that our hearts can be changed and we can turn back to living in a way that conforms to the will of God.

07:51.362 --> 07:55.168
Now also in verse 11 says she is boisterous and rebellious.

07:55.569 --> 07:59.035
Her feet do not remain at home.

07:59.917 --> 08:01.058
She's not content.

08:02.701 --> 08:04.044
The world has no peace.

08:05.766 --> 08:08.030
The world has in reality, no hope.

08:08.932 --> 08:10.535
The world is never content.

08:11.095 --> 08:14.962
And if you give yourself to the world, you will never be content.

08:15.298 --> 08:19.742
You find some of the most famous people in the world and they still are not happy.

08:19.802 --> 08:21.284
They want to be more famous.

08:21.664 --> 08:25.648
You find some of the richest people in the world and they're just not happy.

08:25.908 --> 08:26.869
They want to be richer.

08:27.249 --> 08:31.653
You find people with great power and yet that power is not enough.

08:32.394 --> 08:35.997
They want more power over more people.

08:36.017 --> 08:45.266
It is only in Christ in believing in Him and trusting in Him and in doing His will that we can truly find contentment.

08:45.698 --> 08:53.306
Now, we're in verse 12 now, and this is where we're going to begin our study.

08:54.127 --> 08:57.191
The world is also, and I want you to listen to this very carefully.

08:57.611 --> 08:59.653
The world is predatory.

09:00.835 --> 09:02.316
It is like a predator.

09:03.237 --> 09:07.021
A predator chases down a prey in order to devour it.

09:07.322 --> 09:08.943
Look at verses 12 and 13.

09:08.963 --> 09:14.930
It says, she is now in the streets, now in the squares, and lurks

09:15.234 --> 09:17.097
by every corner.

09:17.217 --> 09:19.059
So she seizes him and kisses him.

09:19.080 --> 09:23.346
And with a brazen face, she says to him certain things to attract him.

09:23.826 --> 09:24.367
But let's look.

09:24.427 --> 09:27.091
First of all, it says the woman is in the streets.

09:27.692 --> 09:33.761
Verse 12, she's prowling around like someone on the hunt.

09:34.742 --> 09:38.167
And then it also says she is lurking at every corner.

09:38.487 --> 09:43.154
Now the word lurk here literally means to lie and wait.

09:43.714 --> 09:48.540
like setting up an ambush, like setting up an ambush.

09:48.560 --> 09:55.189
When I was a boy, of course, on our, I would hunt and fish, but I would also trap.

09:56.270 --> 10:08.366
And you set out traps and you disguise them so that the trap is able to spring before the animal knows that it's actually there.

10:08.866 --> 10:10.228
And that's what she's doing here.

10:10.328 --> 10:11.890
She's setting up an ambush.

10:11.970 --> 10:20.545
She's hiding her true intentions and she's wanting to capture this young man and use him for her own pleasure.

10:21.166 --> 10:22.969
That's a great description of the world.

10:23.630 --> 10:27.456
In verse 13, it says, she seizes him.

10:28.678 --> 10:29.660
She seizes him.

10:30.081 --> 10:36.532
Now the word here means to take hold of, with power, with force, even with violence.

10:36.592 --> 10:37.874
It means to grab

10:37.954 --> 10:42.679
hold of someone and to overcome them and overpower them.

10:42.699 --> 10:43.520
Okay.

10:44.040 --> 10:46.843
The moment she grabs him, she's in control.

10:47.504 --> 10:54.050
You know, my wife, Chado, she sent me, she and I used to go through the jungle everywhere in Peru.

10:54.691 --> 10:59.055
And she sent me a kind of a video this morning.

10:59.776 --> 11:05.682
And it was a Cayman, which is an, an at what you'd call an, I guess, an alligator.

11:06.114 --> 11:09.778
And it was about, I'd say eight feet.

11:10.379 --> 11:12.922
So it was a pretty big alligator.

11:13.763 --> 11:20.512
And all of a sudden, coming out of the shore, out of the bushes, it's a jaguar.

11:21.513 --> 11:32.306
And when I was in the jungle, and I would be with the guys that would hunt and things in the jungle, the, the aguaruna tribe, that they weren't afraid of a lot.

11:32.866 --> 11:36.051
But everyone in the jungle was afraid of a jaguar.

11:36.071 --> 11:41.158
It has the strongest jaw strength, I think, of any cat, even stronger than a lion.

11:42.059 --> 11:50.091
And in this video that my wife sent me, this jaguar just leaps off the bank on top of this huge alligator.

11:51.172 --> 11:54.657
And they're underwater for, I don't like, seem like 10 seconds.

11:55.318 --> 12:00.946
Then they come up out of the water and this jaguar drags that huge alligator onto the beach.

12:01.218 --> 12:04.442
and then just proceeds to, uh, to kill it.

12:06.064 --> 12:09.769
And I can't think of anything more terrifying.

12:10.571 --> 12:18.241
Once that animal gets a hold of you, it's not letting go and there's nothing you can do about it.

12:19.643 --> 12:28.114
And so when you're in the jungle and you're thinking, you know, you're walking through a path and you're just thinking everything is okay and you don't know that

12:28.418 --> 12:39.450
behind you and beside you and around you is this dangerous thing, like a jaguar that once it gets a hold of you, it's not going to let go.

12:39.510 --> 12:40.771
It's going to overpower you.

12:41.212 --> 12:44.535
And that is one of the greatest descriptions of sin.

12:45.677 --> 12:54.386
So when you think of sin, I don't want you to think of it just as something that you would do, like

12:54.466 --> 12:57.029
commit a sinful deed or say a sinful thing.

12:57.369 --> 13:18.352
I want you to think about it as something that is hunting you, something that is after you, a predator, like a jaguar, like an alligator in the swamp, like a shark in the ocean, like if you were the size of a fly caught in a net, caught in a web and a spider was coming after you.

13:18.372 --> 13:24.338
All of these are terrifying, but none of these things I just described are more terrifying.

13:24.834 --> 13:25.495
than sin.

13:26.356 --> 13:42.982
Sin wrecks young people, children, sin wrecks adults, wrecks families, wrecks churches, sin wrecks nations, sin has wrecked the world, the entire human race.

13:43.843 --> 13:50.112
So the world is predatory and sin is a predator.

13:50.553 --> 13:53.778
I want you to listen to this text from Genesis 4, 7.

13:54.338 --> 14:03.552
It says, God told Cain, sin is crouching at the door and its desire is for you.

14:05.014 --> 14:06.096
But you must master it.

14:06.697 --> 14:18.956
So he's saying, sin is at the door of your tent, like a wild animal, like a jaguar, like a, like a ravenous wolf or giant lion.

14:19.417 --> 14:20.739
It's at the door of your tent.

14:21.099 --> 14:22.962
And what is it desires you?

14:23.906 --> 14:26.870
Now, this is not a good desire like it loves you.

14:27.210 --> 14:29.973
This is a hungry desire.

14:29.993 --> 14:34.439
It doesn't care about you at all.

14:36.001 --> 14:41.467
Its only desire is to destroy you, to devour you, to feed upon you.

14:41.868 --> 14:53.842
I was listening to a man one time he was talking about being attacked by a shark and he said, possibly the most terrifying thing is that when you look into the eye of that shark, it's just

14:55.170 --> 15:00.937
Black, emotionalist, it shows no, it has a lack of emotion.

15:00.977 --> 15:03.600
It shows no pity, no compassion.

15:04.861 --> 15:07.524
It only wants to devour you.

15:08.385 --> 15:22.802
And that sin, in Proverbs 5, 22, it says, regarding the fool, it says, his own iniquities will capture the wicked and he will be held with the cords of his sin.

15:23.650 --> 15:27.074
So it entraps him and it holds him.

15:27.094 --> 15:31.961
It's like Gulliver's travels when, you know, he's tied down on the ground and he can't get out.

15:32.541 --> 15:38.930
Or like again, someone trapped into a gigantic spider web from which you cannot remove yourself.

15:39.590 --> 15:45.037
And then you look up and here comes the spider drawing closer and closer and closer.

15:45.258 --> 15:48.562
It's like being tied to a tree out in

15:48.738 --> 15:58.151
Some African plane and all of a sudden you're surrounded by hyena after hyena after hyena and there's absolutely nothing you can do.

15:59.052 --> 16:01.876
Now some of you may be saying, Brother Paul, you shouldn't talk that way.

16:01.916 --> 16:03.197
You're giving us nightmares.

16:04.860 --> 16:06.422
Sometimes nightmares can be good.

16:07.803 --> 16:14.232
Sin destroys everything and it takes no prisoners.

16:14.853 --> 16:16.856
It will devour you.

16:18.037 --> 16:18.738
Let's go on.

16:19.298 --> 16:24.466
So we've said here, I want to make sure sin is a predator.

16:25.167 --> 16:26.489
The world is predatory.

16:26.929 --> 16:35.822
Sin is a predator, but also sometimes sinners, other individuals who are given to sin also act like predators.

16:36.523 --> 16:43.634
Proverbs 4, 16 says this, talking about the wicked, for they cannot sleep unless they do evil.

16:44.555 --> 16:49.202
So there are people out there that their whole life is set to just

16:49.378 --> 16:53.443
doing evil, living in a manner contrary to God.

16:53.763 --> 16:57.308
Now, that in itself is bad enough, but look what else it says.

16:58.329 --> 17:02.274
And they are robbed of sleep unless they make someone stumble.

17:03.396 --> 17:15.310
You see, sinners and a sinful world, the idea is not just that they want to sin and that they do sin, but they want to draw other people into their sin.

17:15.851 --> 17:18.194
It's like when you commit a crime,

17:18.978 --> 17:24.283
When you're living a life of sin, in your conscience, you feel guilty.

17:25.004 --> 17:30.770
But if you can get more people to join you, it somehow calms your conscience.

17:31.071 --> 17:34.854
It soothes your conscience because you're not the only one committing this evil.

17:35.175 --> 17:37.277
You can look around you and see other people doing it.

17:37.737 --> 17:40.600
But on the day of judgment, that won't help you.

17:41.121 --> 17:46.066
That won't help you a bit because you will stand there alone in your evil.

17:46.466 --> 17:48.088
So sinners are predatory.

17:48.409 --> 17:53.816
And then finally, and you need to understand this, the devil is a predator.

17:55.439 --> 18:07.916
Now, you know, a lot of times, young people, when you see pictures and drawings of a devil, it's a little guy in a red suit with a tail and a pitchfork and some horns.

18:08.637 --> 18:15.186
Or maybe you've seen movies you shouldn't have seen, and he's depicted as something far more horrible.

18:16.098 --> 18:17.040
Well, here's the problem.

18:18.802 --> 18:19.864
He is monstrous.

18:20.605 --> 18:21.447
He is gruesome.

18:22.268 --> 18:24.051
He is evil and vile.

18:25.273 --> 18:33.407
Yet for the most part, he portrays himself as quite beautiful, quite attractive.

18:34.689 --> 18:40.338
Someone who can bring pleasure, relief, joy, purpose,

18:41.122 --> 18:51.073
So what you need to realize is that when the devil comes to you to take you away from the paths that God wants you to walk in, he's not going to present himself as a monster.

18:52.274 --> 19:03.747
He's going to present himself as someone delightful, someone attractive, someone who can give you everything your sinful heart desires.

19:04.408 --> 19:05.268
So he's a predator.

19:06.390 --> 19:10.354
So in 1 Peter 5, 8, it says, be of sober spirit.

19:11.554 --> 19:13.777
Beyond the alert, why?

19:14.177 --> 19:21.706
Your adversary, the devil, prowls around like a roaring lion seeking someone to devour.

19:26.572 --> 19:30.917
You know, most of us have never been hunted.

19:34.442 --> 19:38.066
I've heard men talk, men up in the Arctic Circle,

19:39.042 --> 19:45.071
guys who hunt up in Canada about being surrounded by wolves.

19:45.712 --> 19:47.635
And wolves aren't like little dogs.

19:47.715 --> 19:51.380
They're very, very large and very, very dangerous.

19:52.162 --> 19:58.411
Or in Africa, men being surrounded by a pack of lions or a pack of hyenas.

19:59.793 --> 20:04.300
Or in Asia, the gigantic Bengal tiger.

20:04.780 --> 20:08.626
You know, there's some places where people walk down

20:08.802 --> 20:12.146
paths to their, to their farmlands and things like that.

20:12.226 --> 20:15.991
And they actually wear a mask, a human mask on the back of their head.

20:16.431 --> 20:16.711
Why?

20:17.052 --> 20:22.538
Because the tiger will come up where you're not looking and attack you that way.

20:23.319 --> 20:35.634
And so I can't think of anything more terrifying than being hunted, but that's exactly what the devil is doing.

20:36.418 --> 20:41.944
every day all around the world to individuals just like you and me.

20:42.645 --> 20:45.328
And if it's not him, that's the who's who work with him.

20:46.449 --> 20:53.717
Other fallen spirits, but also people who are given to sin and want others to join them.

20:54.498 --> 21:05.010
And the only way that you can really stay safe from this is to study God's Word, to apply God's Word,

21:05.986 --> 21:09.110
to pray, you know, in the Lord's Prayer, what does it say?

21:09.170 --> 21:12.274
Lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from evil.

21:12.995 --> 21:21.907
And one more thing, surround yourself with other Christians who love the Lord and are going to speak into your life.

21:22.588 --> 21:35.826
Now that's primarily within the context of a local church, but also hopefully if you're in a Christian home, your mother and father listening to their advice and guarding it and keeping it,

21:36.130 --> 21:44.701
And then make sure that your friends are the type of people that are going to encourage you to walk with Christ.

21:46.703 --> 21:51.850
You know, there's a, I forget what philosopher said it, but it's a good statement.

21:52.491 --> 21:55.715
If you're the smartest person in the room, you're in the wrong room.

21:56.556 --> 22:04.626
What we mean by that is it's good to associate with people smarter than you because, well, you'll become smarter.

22:05.826 --> 22:08.289
Well, we can turn it with regard to Christianity.

22:08.770 --> 22:12.195
If you're the godliest person in the room, you're in the wrong room.

22:13.156 --> 22:25.272
You want to be with people who have walked with Christ longer than you have, who have grown in their maturity far beyond what you have grown so that they can pull you up to them.

22:26.073 --> 22:35.506
But if you surround yourself with immature Christians or you surround yourself, even worse with people who are not Christians, but given to rebellion

22:35.746 --> 22:37.227
It's going to take its toll on you.

22:38.168 --> 22:40.851
So remember, this is a predatory world.

22:41.652 --> 22:43.173
There are predatory people.

22:43.754 --> 22:46.397
There's definitely a predatory devil.

22:47.658 --> 22:54.264
The only way that we can remain safe is staying within the will of God and that journey.

22:55.345 --> 22:58.148
Well, it's not a lone wolf journey.

22:59.249 --> 23:04.114
We need others around us to speak into our lives.

23:05.026 --> 23:08.571
and to help us as we seek to go on with the Lord.

23:09.412 --> 23:10.894
All right, well, let's go to the Lord in prayer.

23:13.057 --> 23:15.340
Father, thank you for your word.

23:16.682 --> 23:24.373
And I pray, dear God, that you would use it in the life of each and every young person who's listening to these teachings.

23:25.474 --> 23:27.898
Father, please help them.

23:27.918 --> 23:33.906
Please, Lord God, that they would know Christ, and that in knowing Christ, they would love Him.

23:36.834 --> 23:38.937
They would seek to be conformed to his image.

23:38.977 --> 23:43.043
They would seek to know his will and walk in it.

23:44.345 --> 23:52.558
Oh, Father, I pray you raise up a generation of young people who if we were to cut them with a knife, they would bleed the Bible.

23:54.160 --> 23:55.883
Yes, Lord.

23:55.903 --> 23:56.764
In Jesus name.

23:57.545 --> 23:57.906
Amen.

